Radare is a portable reverse engineering framework. It is composed by a set of programs and libraries with bindings for several programming languages.

What can Radare do for you?

* Assemble/Dissemble several architectures
* Local native and Remote Debugger (gdb, r2, winedbg)
* Runs on Linux, *BSD, Windows, OSX, Android, iOS, Solaris and Haiku
* Forensic Filesystem and Carving for Data
* It is written in C and it can be scripted in Python, Javascript, Go and more
* Colaborative analysis using the embedded webserver
* Cryptographic checksumming disk and data images
* Visualize data structures of several file types
* Patch programs to uncover new features or fix vulnerabilities
